<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=G._K._Chesterton&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9" title="Edit section: Literature and biographies on Chesterton">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Literature and biographies on Chesterton</span></h2>
<ul>
<li>Cooney, A., <i>G.K. Chesterton, One Sword at Least</i>, Third Way Publications, London, 1999. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0953507718" class="internal">ISBN 0-9535077-1-8</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Michael_Coren" title="Michael Coren">Coren, M</a>., <i>Gilbert: The Man Who Was G. K. Chesterton</i>, Paragon House, New York, 1990.</li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Michael_ffinch&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Michael ffinch (page does not exist)">ffinch, M.</a>, <i>G. K. Chesterton</i>, 1986</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Hugh_Kenner" title="Hugh Kenner">Kenner, H</a>., <i>Paradox in Chesterton</i>, 1947.</li>
<li><a href="/w/index.php?title=Randall_Paine&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1" class="new" title="Randall Paine (page does not exist)">Paine, R</a>., <i>The Universe and Mr. Chesterton</i>, Sherwood Sugden, 1999. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0893855111" class="internal">ISBN 0893855111</a></li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Joseph_Pearce" title="Joseph Pearce">Pearce, J</a>, <i>Wisdom and Innocence - A Life of G.K.Chesterton</i>, Hodder &amp; Stoughton, London, 1996. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/0340671327" class="internal">ISBN 0-340-67132-7</a></li>
<li>Ward, M., <i>Gilbert Keith Chesterton</i>, Sheed &amp; Ward, 1944.</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/Marshall_McLuhan" title="Marshall McLuhan">Marshall McLuhan</a> wrote an article on G.K. Chesterton, titled "G.K. Chesterton: A Practical <a href="/wiki/Mysticism" title="Mysticism">Mystic</a>" (<i>Dalhousie Review</i> 15 (4), 1936).</li>
<li><a href="/wiki/EWTN" title="EWTN" class="mw-redirect">EWTN</a> features a television series, <a href="http://www.ewtn.com/series/chesterton/index.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.ewtn.com/series/chesterton/index.htm" rel="nofollow"><i>G. K. Chesterton: The Apostle of Common Sense</i></a>, that focuses on Chesterton and his works.</li>
</ul>
